subSubSection.paragraph:
[English name: Painted Scorpionfish] ( Figs. 2 , 3 B, 4 B, 5 B, 6 ;
Tables 1–2
)

Diagnosis. A species of
Parascorpaena
with the following characters: pectoral-fin rays usually 17 (rarely 16 or 18 ); scale rows in longitudinal series 43–49 (mode 45 ); scale rows below lateral line 15–18 ( 16 ); scale rows between last dorsal-fin spine base and lateral line 6–8 ( 7 ); scale rows between sixth dorsal-fin spine base and lateral line 6–8 ( 7 ); first and second suborbital ridges fused, forming a single ridge (
Fig. 5
) with two spines behind level of orbit, spines absent below eye; interorbital ridges poorly developed, not encircling a depression (
Fig. 4
); occipital pit very weakly developed, nearly flat (
Fig. 4
); smaller head and orbit, head length 40.1–46.3 % (mean 43.6 %) of SL and orbit diameter 10.5 –13.0% ( 11.4 %) of SL (
Fig. 6
); shorter upper jaw and pectoral fin, upper-jaw length 20.0–24.0% ( 21.5 %) of SL and longest pectoral-fin ray length 29.5– 36.7 % ( 31.8 %) of SL (
Fig. 6
); no black blotch on spinous portion of dorsal fin.
